Police say when they cornered the man's car, he allegedly shot and killed himself, and the girl's body was also found in the car. JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg police are investigating the murder of a teenage girl in Fourways. Police say they were following up on a tip off on Sunday night. When they managed to corner a vehicle, the driver allegedly shot and killed himself. The police's Mavela Masondo says it was later established that the body of the man's 14-year-old daughter was in the car. “For now, we’re not sure who killed this girl but we’re investigating.”